Package: strsplit
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: split input strings by delimiter and print each item on separate line
 strsplit is a command-line utility that splits input strings by a delimiter
 (default: whitespace) and prints each item on a separate line.
 .
 Features:
  - Custom delimiter regex support
  - Line numbering with configurable base and reset
  - Multiple sorting modes (numeric, version, human-numeric, etc.)
  - Custom output formatting
  - Indentation and run separation options
  - Both stdin and command-line argument input modes
